    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-13T18:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-13T18:55:00-05:00" n="621"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.6111/5–1354: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 621<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d621fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName>, cleared by <persName corresp="#p_BW1"
                            >Barbour</persName> (<gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_EE1">EE</gloss>), and signed for the Secretary by <persName
                            corresp="#p_KJC1">Jeffrey C. Kitchen</persName>. Attached to the source
                        text is a brief typewritten note of May 13 from <persName corresp="#p_BRR1"
                            >Robert R. Bowie</persName> (<gloss target="#t_SP1">S/P</gloss>) to
                            <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> which reads: “Here is a
                        draft of cable to <persName corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName>. It was
                        prepared by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BW1">Barbour</persName> after he and I
                        talked. He thinks it is desirable to give this much detail to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName> about our thinking.” It cannot be
                        determined whether the text printed is the same as that submitted with
                            <persName corresp="#p_BRR1">Bowie</persName>’s memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-13T18:55:00-05:00"
                            >May 13, 1954—6:55 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>716. Eyes only Ambassador from Secretary. Considerable thought has been given
                    here to statements by Marshal <persName corresp="#p_Z1">Zhukov</persName> in <hi
                        rend="italic">Pravda</hi> on occasion armistice commemoration.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d621fn2">See <ref target="#d622fn3">footnote 3, <hi rend="italic"
                                >infra</hi>.</ref>
                    </note> You will recall that there was respect apparently on mutual basis
                    between <persName corresp="#p_Z1">Zhukov</persName> and the President.
                    Suggestions here have been made regarding possible communication by President to
                        <persName corresp="#p_Z1">Zhukov</persName>, possibly on tenth anniversary
                    of opening of second front in Normandy on June 6. Also suggestion has been made
                    as to ascertaining possibility <persName corresp="#p_Z1">Zhukov</persName>
                    visit. Purpose would be possibly to open up some channel of communication which
                    might be less inflexible than <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>
                    appears to be. Would appreciate your reactions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
